Mix water, 2 tablespoons butter, carrots and pepper in saucepan. Heat to a boil. Remove from heat. Add stuffing and mix lightly. Spoon stuffing across center of 3-quart shallow baking dish. Arrange fish on each side of stuffing. Melt remaining butter and mix with lemon juice and parsley. Spoon over fish. Bake at 400 degrees F 15 minutes or until fish is done.